>300 g water<b> in <b>step 1,<b> then in <b>step 2<b> place the cooked pears in sterilised jars and pour the hot spiced wine into the jars to cover the pears. Seal the jars immediately and turn upside down for <b>10 minutes.<b> Preserved pears can be stored refrigerated for a few weeks, and must be eaten within <b>7 days<b> of opening the jar.","For a sweet-savoury combination, serve the pears in red wine with Gorgonzola cheese as a starter or cheese course.","For a faster result, omit <b>step 2<b> and reduce the spiced wine immediately, without marinating the pears. In this case the pears will remain white.","You can replace or add to the spices in the wine according to your preference (e.g. star anise, green anise, vanilla)."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h 20m","6 portions"]}